==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[neighbourhood]]

===Etymology===
[[neighbor]] + [[-hood]]

===Noun===
'''neighborhood'''
# The quality or condition of being a neighbor; the state of  being or dwelling near; proximity.
#* "Then the prison and the palace were in awful neighborhood." &mdash; [[w:Edward Bulwer-Lytton, 1st Baron Lytton|Lord Lytton]].
# A place near; vicinity; adjoining district; a region the inhabitants of which may be counted as neighbors
#: ''He lives in my neighborhood.''
# The inhabitants who live in the vicinity of each other
#: ''The fire alarmed all the neighborhood.''
# (''obsolete'') The disposition becoming a neighbor; neighborly kindness or good will. 

====Synonyms====
* [[vicinity]]
* [[proximity]]

====Related terms====
* [[microneighborhood]]

====Usage notes====
* [[Neighborhood]] is Anglo-Saxon, and [[vicinity]] is Latin. [[Vicinity]] does not commonly denote as close a connection as [[neighborhood]] does.  A neighborhood is a more immediately vicinity. The houses immediately adjoining a square are in the neighborhood of that square; those which are somewhat further removed are also in the vicinity of the square.

